header.gameNote: SEC WOMEN'S TOURNAMENT - QUARTERFINALS AT NASHVILLE TN

article.headline: Vanderbilt 69, Mississippi St. 55
article.story:
NASHVILLE, Tenn. --  Tiffany Clarke scored all of her 23 points in the second half, and Vanderbilt beat Mississippi State 69-55 Friday night in the Southeastern Conference tournament quarterfinals.

Vanderbilt (20-10) advanced to the semifinals for the fifth straight season, and the Commodores also won at least one game in this tournament for a 12th straight year. They will play No. 16 Kentucky in the semifinals Saturday.

No. 11 seed Mississippi State had the lone upset through the first two days of the tournament, but the Lady Bulldogs just couldn't shoot well enough to keep pace with Vanderbilt in the teams' first game in this event since 1997.

Angela Puleo scored 11 points, and Hannah Tuomi had 10 for Vanderbilt.

Diamber Johnson led the Lady Bulldogs with 20 points.
